# Book: Luke

# Section: Since many have undertaken
# Luke 01:01
Since many have undertaken
  to set in order a narrative
    concerning those matters
      which have been fulfilled among us,
# Luke 01:02
even as those who from the beginning
  were eyewitnesses and servants of the word
    delivered them to us,
# Luke 01:03
it seemed good to me also,
  having traced the course of all things accurately
  from the first,
to write to you in order,
  most excellent Theophilus;
# Luke 01:04
that you might know the certainty
  concerning the things in which you were instructed.

# Section: There was in the days of Herod
# Luke 01:05
STARTHERE

There was in the days of Herod,
the king of Judea,
a certain priest named Zacharias,
of the priestly division of Abijah.

He had a wife of the daughters of Aaron,
and her name was Elizabeth.

# Luke 01:06
They were both righteous before God,
walking blamelessly
in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord.

# Luke 01:07
But they had no child,
because Elizabeth was barren,
and they both were well advanced in years.

# Luke 01:08
Now while he executed the priest's office before God in the order of his division

# Luke 01:09
according to the custom of the priest's office,
his lot was to enter into the temple of the Lord and burn incense.

# Luke 01:10
The whole multitude of the people were praying outside at the hour of incense.

# Luke 01:11
An angel of the Lord appeared to him,
standing on the right side of the altar of incense.

# Luke 01:12
Zacharias was troubled when he saw him,
and fear fell upon him.

# Luke 01:13
But the angel said to him,
``Don’t be afraid,
Zacharias,
because your request has been heard.

Your wife,
Elizabeth,
will bear you a son,
and you shall call his name John.

# Luke 01:14
You will have joy and gladness,
and many will rejoice at his birth.

# Luke 01:15
For he will be great in the sight of the Lord,
and he will drink no wine nor strong drink.

He will be filled with the Holy Spirit,
even from his mother's womb.

# Luke 01:16
He will turn many of the children of Israel to the Lord their God.

# Luke 01:17
He will go before him in the spirit and power of Elijah,
‘to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children,’ and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just;
to prepare a people prepared for the Lord.''

# Luke 01:18
Zacharias said to the angel,
``How can I be sure of this?

For I am an old man,
and my wife is well advanced in years.''

# Luke 01:19
The angel answered him,
``I am Gabriel,
who stands in the presence of God.

I was sent to speak to you and to bring you this good news.

# Luke 01:20
Behold,
you will be silent and not able to speak until the day that these things will happen,
because you didn’t believe my words,
which will be fulfilled in their proper time.''

# Luke 01:21
The people were waiting for Zacharias,
and they marveled that he delayed in the temple.

# Luke 01:22
When he came out,
he could not speak to them.

They perceived that he had seen a vision in the temple.

He continued making signs to them,
and remained mute.

# Luke 01:23
When the days of his service were fulfilled,
he departed to his house.

# Luke 01:24
After these days Elizabeth his wife conceived,
and she hid herself five months,
saying,

# Luke 01:25
``Thus has the Lord done to me in the days in which he looked at me,
to take away my reproach among men.''

# Luke 01:26
Now in the sixth month,
the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a city of Galilee named Nazareth,

# Luke 01:27
to a virgin pledged to be married to a man whose name was Joseph,
of David's house.

The virgin's name was Mary.

# Luke 01:28
Having come in,
the angel said to her,
{
  Rejoice,
  you highly favored one!

  The Lord is with you.

  Blessed are you among women!
}

# Luke 01:29
But when she saw him,
she was greatly troubled at the saying,
and considered what kind of salutation this might be.

# Luke 01:30
The angel said to her,
{
  Don't be afraid,
Mary,
  for you have found favor with God.

  # Luke 01:31
  Behold,
  you will conceive in your womb
  and give birth to a son,
  and shall name him `Jesus.'

  # Luke 01:32
  He will be great
  and will be called the Son of the Most High.

  The Lord God will give him the throne of his father David,
  # Luke 01:33
  and he will reign over the house of Jacob forever.

  There will be no end to his Kingdom.
}

# Luke 01:34
Mary said to the angel,
``How can this be,
seeing I am a virgin?''

# Luke 01:35
The angel answered her,
``The Holy Spirit will come on you,
and the power of the Most High will overshadow you.

Therefore also the holy one who is born from you will be called the Son of God.

# Luke 01:36
Behold,
Elizabeth your relative also has conceived a son in her old age;
and this is the sixth month with her who was called barren.

# Luke 01:37
For nothing spoken by God is impossible.''

# Luke 01:38
Mary said,
``Behold,
the servant of the Lord;
let it be done to me according to your word.''

Then the angel departed from her.

# Luke 01:39
Mary arose in those days and went into the hill country with haste,
into a city of Judah,

# Luke 01:40
and entered into the house of Zacharias and greeted Elizabeth.

# Luke 01:41
When Elizabeth heard Mary's greeting,
the baby leaped in her womb;
and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.

# Luke 01:42
She called out with a loud voice and said,
``Blessed are you among women,
and blessed is the fruit of your womb!

# Luke 01:43
Why am I so favored,
that the mother of my Lord should come to me?

# Luke 01:44
For behold,
when the voice of your greeting came into my ears,
the baby leaped in my womb for joy!

# Luke 01:45
Blessed is she who believed,
for there will be a fulfillment of the things which have been spoken to her from the Lord!''

# Luke 01:46
Mary said,
``My soul magnifies the Lord.

# Luke 01:47
My spirit has rejoiced in God my Savior,

# Luke 01:48
for he has looked at the humble state of his servant.

For behold,
from now on,
all generations will call me blessed.

# Luke 01:49
For he who is mighty has done great things for me.

Holy is his name.

# Luke 01:50
His mercy is for generations and generations on those who fear him.

# Luke 01:51
He has shown strength with his arm.

He has scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.

# Luke 01:52
He has put down princes from their thrones,
and has exalted the lowly.

# Luke 01:53
He has filled the hungry with good things.

He has sent the rich away empty.

# Luke 01:54
He has given help to Israel,
his servant,
that he might remember mercy,

# Luke 01:55
as he spoke to our fathers,
to Abraham and his offspring forever.''

# Luke 01:56
Mary stayed with her about three months,
and then returned to her house.

# Luke 01:57
Now the time that Elizabeth should give birth was fulfilled,
and she gave birth to a son.

# Luke 01:58
Her neighbors and her relatives heard that the Lord had magnified his mercy toward her,
and they rejoiced with her.

# Luke 01:59
On the eighth day,
they came to circumcise the child;
and they would have called him Zacharias,
after the name of his father.

# Luke 01:60
His mother answered,
``Not so;
but he will be called John.''

# Luke 01:61
They said to her,
``There is no one among your relatives who is called by this name.''

# Luke 01:62
They made signs to his father,
what he would have him called.

# Luke 01:63
He asked for a writing tablet,
and wrote,
{
  His name is John.
}

They all marveled.

# Luke 01:64
His mouth was opened immediately and his tongue freed,
and he spoke,
blessing God.

# Luke 01:65
Fear came on all who lived around them,
and all these sayings were talked about
throughout all the hill country of Judea.

# Luke 01:66
All who heard them laid them up in their heart,
saying,
{
  What then will this child be?
}

The hand of the Lord was with him.

# Luke 01:67
His father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Spirit,
and prophesied,
saying,

# Luke 01:68
``Blessed be the Lord,
the God of Israel,
for he has visited and redeemed his people;

# Luke 01:69
and has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David

# Luke 01:70
(as he spoke by the mouth of his holy prophets who have been from of old),
# Luke 01:71
salvation from our enemies
and from the hand of all who hate us;
# Luke 01:72
to show mercy toward our fathers,
to remember his holy covenant,
# Luke 01:73
the oath which he swore to Abraham our father,
# Luke 01:74
to grant to us that we,
being delivered out of the hand of our enemies,
should serve him without fear,
# Luke 01:75
in holiness and righteousness
before him all the days of our life.

# Luke 01:76
And you,
child,
will be called a prophet of the Most High;
for you will go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways,

# Luke 01:77
to give knowledge of salvation to his people by the remission of their sins,

# Luke 01:78
because of the tender mercy of our God,
by which the dawn from on high will visit us,

# Luke 01:79
to shine on those who sit in darkness and the shadow of death;
to guide our feet into the way of peace.''

# Luke 01:80
The child was growing and becoming strong in spirit,
and was in the desert until the day of his public appearance to Israel.

# Luke 01:81
Luke.

# Luke 02:01
Now in those days,
a decree went out from Caesar Augustus
that all the world should be enrolled.

# Luke 02:02
This was the first enrollment made when Quirinius was governor of Syria.

# Luke 02:03
All went to enroll themselves,
everyone to his own city.

# Luke 02:04
Joseph also went up from Galilee,
out of the city of Nazareth,
into Judea,
to David's city,
which is called Bethlehem,
because he was of the house and family of David,

# Luke 02:05
to enroll himself with Mary,
who was pledged to be married to him as wife,
being pregnant.

# Luke 02:06
While they were there,
the day had come for her to give birth.

# Luke 02:07
She gave birth to her firstborn son.

She wrapped him in bands of cloth and laid him in a feeding trough,
because there was no room for them in the inn.

# Luke 02:08
There were shepherds in the same country staying in the field,
and keeping watch by night over their flock.

# Luke 02:09
Behold,
an angel of the Lord stood by them,
and the glory of the Lord shone around them,
and they were terrified.

# Luke 02:10
The angel said to them,
{
  Don’t be afraid,
  for behold,
  I bring you good news of great joy
  which will be to all the people.

  # Luke 02:11
  For there is born to you today,
  in David's city,
  a Savior,
  who is Christ the Lord.

  # Luke 02:12
  This is the sign to you:
  you will find a baby wrapped in strips of cloth,
  lying in a feeding trough.
}

# Luke 02:13
Suddenly,
there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly army praising God and saying,

# Luke 02:14
``Glory to God in the highest,
on earth peace,
good will toward men.''

# Luke 02:15
When the angels went away from them into the sky,
the shepherds said to one another,
``Let's go to Bethlehem,
now,
and see this thing that has happened,
which the Lord has made known to us.''

# Luke 02:16
They came with haste and found both Mary and Joseph,
and the baby was lying in the feeding trough.

# Luke 02:17
When they saw it,
they publicized widely the saying which was spoken to them about this child.

# Luke 02:18
All who heard it wondered at the things
which were spoken to them by the shepherds.

# Luke 02:19
But Mary kept all these sayings,
pondering them in her heart.

# Luke 02:20
The shepherds returned,
glorifying and praising God
for all the things that they had heard and seen,
just as it was told them.

# Luke 02:21
When eight days were fulfilled for the circumcision of the child,
his name was called Jesus,
which was given by the angel before he was conceived in the womb.

# Luke 02:22
When the days of their purification according to the law of Moses were fulfilled,
they brought him up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord
# Luke 02:23
(as it is written in the law of the Lord,
``Every male who opens the womb shall be called holy to the Lord''),
# Luke 02:24
and to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord,
``A pair of turtledoves,
or two young pigeons.''

# Luke 02:25
Behold,
there was a man in Jerusalem whose name was Simeon.

This man was righteous and devout,
looking for the consolation of Israel,
and the Holy Spirit was on him.

# Luke 02:26
It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he should not see death before he had seen the Lord's Christ.

# Luke 02:27
He came in the Spirit into the temple.

When the parents brought in the child,
Jesus,
that they might do concerning him according to the custom of the law,

# Luke 02:28
then he received him into his arms and blessed God,
and said,

# Luke 02:29
{
  Now you are releasing your servant,
  Master,
  according to your word,
  in peace;
  # Luke 02:30
  for my eyes have seen your salvation,
  # Luke 02:31
  which you have prepared
  before the face of all peoples;
  # Luke 02:32
  a light for revelation to the nations,
  and the glory of your people Israel.
}

# Luke 02:33
Joseph and his mother were marveling at the things which were spoken concerning him.

# Luke 02:34
Simeon blessed them,
and said to Mary,
his mother,
``Behold,
this child is appointed for the falling and the rising of many in Israel,
and for a sign which is spoken against.

# Luke 02:35
Yes,
a sword will pierce through your own soul,
that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.''

# Luke 02:36
There was one Anna,
a prophetess,
the daughter of Phanuel,
of the tribe of Asher (she was of a great age,
having lived with a husband seven years from her virginity,

# Luke 02:37
and she had been a widow for about eighty-four years),
who didn’t depart from the temple,
worshiping with fastings and petitions night and day.

# Luke 02:38
Coming up at that very hour,
she gave thanks to the Lord,
and spoke of him
to all those who were looking for redemption in Jerusalem.

# Luke 02:39
When they had accomplished all things
that were according to the law of the Lord,
they returned into Galilee,
to their own city,
Nazareth.

# Luke 02:40
The child was growing,
and was becoming strong in spirit,
being filled with wisdom,
and the grace of God was upon him.

# Luke 02:41
His parents went every year to Jerusalem at the feast of the Passover.

# Luke 02:42
When he was twelve years old,
they went up to Jerusalem according to the custom of the feast;

# Luke 02:43
and when they had fulfilled the days,
as they were returning,
the boy Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem.

Joseph and his mother didn’t know it,

# Luke 02:44
but supposing him to be in the company,
they went a day's journey;
and they looked for him among their relatives and acquaintances.

# Luke 02:45
When they didn’t find him,
they returned to Jerusalem,
looking for him.

# Luke 02:46
After three days they found him in the temple,
sitting in the middle of the teachers,
both listening to them and asking them questions.

# Luke 02:47
All who heard him were amazed
at his understanding and his answers.

# Luke 02:48
When they saw him,
they were astonished;
and his mother said to him,
``Son,
why have you treated us this way?

Behold,
your father and I were anxiously looking for you.''

# Luke 02:49
He said to them,
``Why were you looking for me?

Didn’t you know that I must be in my Father's house?''

# Luke 02:50
They didn’t understand the saying which he spoke to them.

# Luke 02:51
And he went down with them and came to Nazareth.

He was subject to them,
and his mother kept all these sayings in her heart.

# Luke 02:52
And Jesus increased in wisdom and stature,
and in favor with God and men.

